Process Hazard Analysis

The Refinery has a comprehensive program to help ensure that hazards associated with the various processes are identified and controlled. Within this program, each process is systematically examined to identify hazards and ensure that adequate controls are in place to manage these hazards. The Refinery primarily uses the Knowledge-Based and Guideword Hazard and Operability (HAZOP) studies to perform these evaluations. HAZOP analysis is recognized as a systematic and thorough hazard evaluation technique. These analyses are conducted using a team of people who have operating experience and engineering expertise on the process to be evaluated. The PHA team identifies and evaluates hazards on the process, as well as accident prevention and mitigation measures, and makes suggestions for additional prevention and/or mitigation measures when the team believes such measures are necessary.

To ensure that the process controls are consistent with design safety features, the Refinery periodically updates and revalidates the hazard analysis results. In addition to these periodic reviews, hazard reviews are also performed during the design stage of new facilities and for facilities undergoing significant modification.

